From 545c0d4627218bdda2fbd93de12a757adbe6c913 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Blakestream-GaintB <sid@blakestream.local>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 16:56:11 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] v2 Path B: per-ASC routing via filtered-pop on global queue
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Lifted on top of v1 patches 1+2+4+5 (commit c27eed1). Implements
ascpool API + per-ASC pool routing with same-algo failover, but
KEEPS the global staged_work queue model intact — the prior per-pool
queue rewrite (Path A) caused a generator-thread starvation deadlock
and required reflashing the SD card to recover. Path B (filtered-pop
on the global queue) makes that deadlock class structurally impossible.

Files changed (vs c27eed1, source only):
  api.c           +86  ascpool command + Primary/Effective/Failover stats
  api.h            +7  MSG_ASC* codes (Path A compatible)
  driver-baikal.h  +8  BAIKAL_POOL_UNSET + pin helper decls
  driver-baikalu.c +132 pin storage + helpers + seed-on-detect + stats
  miner.h          +3  cgpu_info pin metadata; NO struct pool changes
  sgminer.c       +347 failover helpers + filtered-pop hash_pop_pool +
                       per-pool watermark in gen_thread + Baikal pin
                       short-circuit in get_work_prepare_thread

vs Path A (the abandoned per-pool-queue branch) the differences:
- struct pool staged_work / staged_work_count / staged_rollable not added
- hash_pop_pool walks GLOBAL staged_work with target_pool filter,
  not per-pool queue heads
- clone_available, hash_push, clear_pool_work, discard_stale,
  __total_staged unchanged from v1
- gen_thread main(): existing v1 logic + new
  pool_with_routed_deficit_locked() probe before sleep, deficit_pool
  override of select_pool() when staging
- select_baikal_failover_pool_locked tiebreaker drops staged_work_count
  comparison (no per-pool count to read), uses pool->prio as final
  tiebreaker

Built natively on the live device (Pi Zero, gcc 5.4 from Xenial,
1 GB swap added) at /home/baikal/sgminer-pathb/src/sgminer
sha256 46431e06d9e3ea4ac852f66930a16764132a3ea97e021fcc628bda43f6b93449

Smoke test: --version OK, nm shows baikal_pin_pool /
baikal_clear_pool_pin / hash_pop_pool, strings shows ascpool +
'pinned to pool' + 'cleared pool pin'.

Live-device routing test deferred until human approves a controlled
deploy with --api-port 4029 (separate from v1's 4028) so the
working v1 miner stays up as a safety net during validation.
